cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.SI 

This paper focuses on Spoken Language Understanding (SLU) using deep recurrent neural networks (RNNs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The use of deep neural networks also suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), which covers the development of algorithms and models for machine learning. Additionally, the paper proposes novel RNN architectures, indicating that it could also fit into cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which covers research on intelligent agents and systems. The use of corpora for evaluation suggests that it could also belong to cs.SD (Sound), which covers research on audio and speech processing. Finally, the focus on spoken dialog systems suggests that it could also fit into cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which covers research on social networks and information systems.
